rents of modern history.Ahmad was the first to recognize that former ally Osama bin Laden would turn against the United States. He anticipated the rapidly shifting loyalties of terrorists and understood that overthrowing Saddam Hussein would provoke violence and sectarian strife in Iraq. Ahmad had great compassion for the victims of the proxy wars waged by the leading Cold War powers, and he frequently championed unpopular causes, such as the need to extend the rights of Palestinians and protect Bosnians and Kosovars in a disintegrating Yugoslavia. Toward the end of his life, Ahmad worked tirelessly to broker a peace between India and Pakistan and to prevent the spread of nuclear weapons throughout the subcontinent. As novel and necessary as ever, Ahmad's remarkable vision is here preserved and extended to reveal the extent to which he was involved in the political and historical conflicts of his time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aIslam and politicsxHistoryy20th century. 0aJournalistsvBiography. 0aPacifistsvBiography. 0aPolitical activistszPakistanvBiography. 0aPolitical activistszPakistanxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical activistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPolitical activistszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical scientistsvBiography. 0aSocial changexHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld politicsy1945-1989. 0aWorld politicsy1989- 0aWorld politicsy1989-. 70(DE-601)1060834060(DE-588)4076229-4aPolitische Wissenschaft2gnd 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106658640 cprintz978023117156440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231539920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231539920/original  a978-3-11-066586-4  Co